<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="471" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1151,1933]" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,553,1151,1176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">
Description of the male 
<typeStatus box="[443,548,1151,1176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[561,684,1151,1176]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">Coloration</emphasis>
. Pale brown. Head and pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[1088,1190,1151,1176]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,968,990]" captionTargetBox="[170,1420,209,930]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,946]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Pedionis (Pedionis) aculeata sp. nov. Male holotype. 1. Habitus, dorsal view; 2. Habitus, lateral view; 3. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. Face, facial view. Scale bars: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228902/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">Figs 1, 3</figureCitation>
) with numerous dark brown spots. Scutellum (
<figureCitation box="[442,581,1188,1213]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,968,990]" captionTargetBox="[170,1420,209,930]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,946]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Pedionis (Pedionis) aculeata sp. nov. Male holotype. 1. Habitus, dorsal view; 2. Habitus, lateral view; 3. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. Face, facial view. Scale bars: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228902/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">
Figs 1, 2, 
<number box="[567,581,1188,1212]" pageId="2" pageNumber="471" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
) with dark brown basal triangles. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[1117,1189,1188,1213]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,968,990]" captionTargetBox="[170,1420,209,930]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,946]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Pedionis (Pedionis) aculeata sp. nov. Male holotype. 1. Habitus, dorsal view; 2. Habitus, lateral view; 3. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. Face, facial view. Scale bars: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228902/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">
Fig. 
<number box="[1174,1189,1188,1212]" pageId="2" pageNumber="471" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
) brown with oblique fenestra across midlength hyaline, numerous dark spots in each subapical cells, venation dark brown with white spots. Legs brown with dark brown spots.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1151,1933]" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">
<emphasis box="[199,363,1295,1320]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">Male genitalia</emphasis>
. Pygophore (
<figureCitation box="[512,579,1295,1320]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1312,1334]" captionTargetBox="[162,1427,193,1276]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,175,1290]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 16. Pedionis (Pedionis) aculeata sp. nov. Male holotype. 9. Genital capsule, lateral view; 10. Style, lateral view; 11. Aedeagus, lateral view; 12. Aedeagus, ventral view; 13. Connective, lateral view; 14. Connective, ventral view; 15. Dorsal connective, lateral view; 16. Dorsal connective, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228904/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">
Fig. 
<number box="[564,579,1296,1320]" pageId="2" pageNumber="471" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
) elongate triangular, in lateral view, the apex of caudal margin concave, with row of short sparse setae along ventral surface. Subgenital (
<figureCitation box="[823,892,1332,1357]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1312,1334]" captionTargetBox="[162,1427,193,1276]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,175,1290]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 16. Pedionis (Pedionis) aculeata sp. nov. Male holotype. 9. Genital capsule, lateral view; 10. Style, lateral view; 11. Aedeagus, lateral view; 12. Aedeagus, ventral view; 13. Connective, lateral view; 14. Connective, ventral view; 15. Dorsal connective, lateral view; 16. Dorsal connective, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228904/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">
Fig. 
<number box="[877,892,1332,1356]" pageId="2" pageNumber="471" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
) plate narrow and short, about 
<number box="[1245,1280,1332,1357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="471" value="0.5">0.5</number>
times as long as ventra margin of pygophore; in lateral view, slightly curved dorsally, of uniform width; apex with long marginal setae. Aedeagal (
<figureCitation box="[344,473,1404,1429]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1312,1334]" captionTargetBox="[162,1427,193,1276]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,175,1290]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 16. Pedionis (Pedionis) aculeata sp. nov. Male holotype. 9. Genital capsule, lateral view; 10. Style, lateral view; 11. Aedeagus, lateral view; 12. Aedeagus, ventral view; 13. Connective, lateral view; 14. Connective, ventral view; 15. Dorsal connective, lateral view; 16. Dorsal connective, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228904/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">Figs 11, 12</figureCitation>
) shaft in dorsal view, sinuate towards apex, in lateral view, sinuate sinuately curved, deeply concave on the ventral margin, a large triangular expansion along the dorsal margin; subapical lateral margin with row of small spinal processes; dorsal connective (
<figureCitation box="[857,987,1476,1501]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1312,1334]" captionTargetBox="[162,1427,193,1276]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,175,1290]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 16. Pedionis (Pedionis) aculeata sp. nov. Male holotype. 9. Genital capsule, lateral view; 10. Style, lateral view; 11. Aedeagus, lateral view; 12. Aedeagus, ventral view; 13. Connective, lateral view; 14. Connective, ventral view; 15. Dorsal connective, lateral view; 16. Dorsal connective, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228904/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">Figs 15, 16</figureCitation>
) simple, distal part curved with smooth margins.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1151,1933]" box="[199,714,1548,1573]" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,1548,1573]" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">Female.</emphasis>
Similar in overall coloration to male.
</paragraph>
