<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="471" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1151,1933]" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1799,1824]" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang &amp; Viraktamath" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Viraktamath" box="[638,1079,1799,1824]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pedionis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="471" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinata">
<emphasis box="[638,825,1799,1824]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">Pedionis spinata</emphasis>
Zhang &amp; Viraktamath
</taxonomicName>
externally, but differs in having short subgenital plate which about half as long as ventral margin of pygophore; sinuate aedeagal shaft with row of small spinal processes subapically and distal part dorsal connective with margins smooth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1261,1908,1933]" pageId="2" pageNumber="471" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1151,1933]" box="[199,1261,1908,1933]" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1908,1933]" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name, 
<emphasis box="[559,653,1908,1933]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">aculeate</emphasis>
, refers to aedeagal shaft with row of spinal processes.
</paragraph>
